=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Welcome back to Dry Powder. I=E2=80=99m <s=
trong>Bill
Cohan</strong>.<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The i=
rrepressible hedge fund manager <strong>Bill Ackman </strong>has never been=
 shy about his desire to be mentioned in the same breath as his hero <stron=
g>Warren Buffett</strong>, the Berkshire Hathaway chairman and perhaps the =
greatest investor of all time. This week, I called up Bill to discuss his l=
atest deal proposal=E2=80=94to turn the Howard Hughes Corporation, a fairly=
 successful real estate developer that he=E2=80=99s owned a big stake
in for years, into his own version of Berkshire Hathaway=E2=80=94and how he=
=E2=80=99s hoping to earn his place alongside Buffett on Wall Street=E2=80=
=99s Mount Rushmore.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;"><em>But first=E2=80=A6</em></p></div>
