bottom:32px;"><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;In=
ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In our conversation, Bill told me that the Howa=
rd Hughes proposal
was born out of his frustration with how the company has performed in the p=
ublic markets ever since he spun it out 14 years ago from another company h=
e owned=E2=80=94General Growth Properties=E2=80=94and on which he made a ki=
lling, buying its distressed bonds and converting them into equity in the c=
ompany. He kept hoping Howard Hughes would trade better as a public company=
, even as he kept narrowing its focus. At one point, in 2019, he ran a proc=
ess to sell the company, but no one showed up to buy it.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">Howard Hughes used to own the South Street Seaport, for in=
stance. Bill thought, when he spun off that landmark property last year, th=
at the company=E2=80=99s stock would trade up. Instead, it traded down. =E2=
=80=9CWe really worked hard to refine it and make it into an amazing, inter=
esting business,=E2=80=9D he told me. =E2=80=9CAnd I think it really is an =
amazing and interesting business, but it=E2=80=99s never caught on in Wall =
Street land.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The disconnect between Bill=E2=80=
=99s appraisal of the stock and the market=E2=80=99s valuation of it got hi=
m thinking. As he explained last year on <strong>Lex Fridman</strong>=E2=80=
=99s podcast, =E2=80=9CMost of what I=E2=80=99ve learned in the investment =
business I=E2=80=99ve learned from Warren Buffett. He=E2=80=99s been my gre=
at professor of this business.=E2=80=9D And the number one lesson Ackman to=
ok from his idol: =E2=80=9CWhen the lemmings are running over the cliff, th=
at=E2=80=99s
the time where you=E2=80=99re facing the other direction and you=E2=80=99re=
 running in the other direction. =E2=80=A6 You have to get excited when thi=
ngs get cheaper.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Anyway, given all the cash =
Bill made from owning General Growth, he=E2=80=99s really just been playing=
 with house money with Howard Hughes. So he decided he should just buy the =
rest of the company. Last August, he filed a 13D to telegraph his intention=
s. He hired
Jefferies, the investment bank, and talked to the other investors in the co=
mpany. He said they told him, <em>We kind of wanted to invest with you in t=
his thing, and you=E2=80=99re taking it private. Is there any way you could=
 leave part of it public, so we can go along for the ride?</em> That=E2=80=
=99s when he hatched the plan to keep Howard Hughes public but take greater=
 control of it, and use it as his new, shiny, Berkshire-like investment veh=
icle. (He says he hasn=E2=80=99t spoken with Buffett about his
proposal.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Ackman=E2=80=99s plan would leave exis=
ting Howard Hughes management in place at the operating level, and create a=
 holding company above it to redeploy the cash generated by Howard Hughes i=
n the way Bill wants. He=E2=80=99d be C.E.O. of the holding company, and pu=
t his hedge fund=E2=80=99s management team in place around him to sift thro=
ugh investment opportunities and manage that business.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">He won=E2=80=99t be working for free, of course. He intends to charge=
 Howard Hughes an annual management fee, paid quarterly, of 1.5 percent of =
the company=E2=80=99s equity value. Right now, with Howard Hughes=E2=80=99s=
 market value at $4 billion, Ackman=E2=80=99s annual fee would be $60 milli=
on. That number would increase along with the company=E2=80=99s equity valu=
e. At that price, Bill thinks, the company would be getting him at a bargai=
n.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">=C2=A0</p></div>
